This directory keeps the cpp source code of file2sliceD CLI command,
which is written for splitting a single data file into a series of
small files (slices) according to the first column of the datafile.

The usage can be found by simply type file2sliceD on any terminal.

Note:
	1: to access the binary data by MATLAB/Octave
		fid = fopen('filename','r');
		a   = fread(fid, [npart, 6], 'double')
	2: Jan. 28th, 2013
	---> add option (somflag) for control the output format
	---> somflag: single or multiple files, wheather split to 
				  multiple files or just one single one.
